No, pressing enter doesn't do anything and I have to interrupt with ctrl-C. There is also no error outputs before that (in some runs there were warnings only, but there is nothing after it says building 'torch._C' extension which is where it gets stuck). 

I also ran the same setup with only NUM_JOBS=1 in setup.py but the behavior is very similar, it gets stuck on one of the builds of torch._C.
